      "→ 0`, `y ≠ 0`, and for sufficiently large `k`, `g(k) ≠ 0`.\n\nBut perhaps we can use `Filter.Tendsto.comp` as follows:\n\n`(tendsto f (𝓝[≠] a) (𝓝 1))`. \n\nBut we have that `Tendsto g atTop (𝓝 0)`, so we need a subset of the neighborhood. \n\nAlternatively, we could first show that `Tendsto g atTop (𝓝[≠] 0)` because eventually `g(k) ≠ 0`.\n\nBut perhaps better to:\n\n1. Note that for `k : ℕ`, `k ≥ 1",
      "\n  have h₁ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => (Real.sin (r * x)) / x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 r) := by\n    have h₂ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => Real.sin (r * x)) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 (Real.sin (r * (0 : ℝ)))) := by\n      apply Continuous.continuousAt\n      exact Real.continuous_sin.comp (continuous_const.mul continuous_id)\n    have h₃ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 0) := by\n      have h₄ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 0) := by\n        apply tendsto_nhdsWithin_of_tendsto_nhds\n        exact continuous_id.tendsto 0\n      exact h₄\n    have h₅ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => (Real.sin (r * x)) / x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 r) := by\n      have h₆ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => (Real.sin (r * x)) / x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 r) := by\n        have h₇ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => Real.sin (r * x)) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0) := by\n          have h₈ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => Real.sin (r * x)) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 (Real.sin (r * (0 : ℝ)))) := by\n            apply Continuous.continuousAt\n            exact Real.continuous_sin.comp (continuous_const.mul continuous_id)\n          have h₉ : Real.sin (r * (0 : ℝ)) = 0 := by norm_num\n          have h₁₀ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => Real.sin (r * x)) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0) := by\n            simpa [h₉] using h₈\n          exact h₁₀\n        have h₁₁ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => x) (𝓝 0) (𝓝 0) := continuous_id.tendsto 0\n        have h₁₂ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => (Real.sin (r * x)) / x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 r) := by\n          -- Use the fact that the limit of sin(x)/x as x → 0 is 1 to find the limit of sin(r * x)/x as x → 0\n          have h₁₃ : Tendsto (fun x : ℝ => (Real.sin (r * x)) / x) (𝓝[≠] 0) (𝓝 r) := by\n            have h₁₄ : (fun x : ℝ => (Real.sin (r * x)) / x) = (fun x : ℝ => r * (Real.sin (r * x) / (r * x))) := by\n              funext x\n              by_cases hx : r = 0\n              · simp_all\n              · have h₁₅ : x ≠ 0 := by\n                  intro h\n                  simp_all [hx]\n                field_simp [hx, h₁₅]\n                <;> ring_nf\n                <;> field_simp [hx, h₁₅]\n                <;> ring_